        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 1 at 7:18PM CDT until May 1 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Western Oldham County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southwestern Hartley County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 800 PM CDT.

* At 718 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 4 miles northeast of Nara Visa to 13 miles southwest
of Romero to 18 miles northeast of Logan, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

* These severe thunderstorms will remain over mainly rural areas of
western Oldham and southwestern Hartley Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
